cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised deep learning approach, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses tracklet data, which is a common technique in multimedia analysis, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of scalability in practical re-id deployment, which could be considered a security issue, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
